Download summary

Schoople provides a number of useful services
that save time and money whilst raising money for the school.

Improving school/parent communications
ParentMessage is an online message board for schools. Messages can be filtered by year groups and automatic notifications sent to parents. Parents can comment on posts, turning the message board into a useful feedback forum.
Taking school fundraising further
In association with WorldPay, FundWider gives school fundraising projects a specific purpose, target and deadline. It provides an online showcase, enabling donations from a wider audience including local businesses.
Watch the FundWider video

But don't take our word for it...

Natalie Halsall, Parent
Wayland Academy
Norfolk
"I receive notifications about posts that are relevant to me without having to trawl through every message - brilliant"
Janet Pascoe, Headteacher
St Buryan Academy
Cornwall
"It’s such an easy way to get messages to our parents - ParentMessage automatically notifies parents about new posts. The feedback facility saves loads of time spent emailing back and forth with parents"
‹ ›
Rae Lowe, Business Manager
West Newcastle Academy
Newcastle upon Tyne
"Local businesses donated online and we exceeded our target."
James Singh, School Fundraiser
William Bellamy Primary School
Essex
"The site had everything we needed to spread the word and we raised an incredible £2,500 in just one term."
